{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Escape Once Filter - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Escape Once Filter</h1>

<p>Escapes HTML special characters in a string without double-escaping content that is already escaped.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ value | escape_once }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ "<script>" | escape_once }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> &amp;lt;script&amp;gt;</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ "&amp;lt;already escaped&amp;gt;" | escape_once }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> &amp;lt;already escaped&amp;gt; (not double-escaped)</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<p>If the string already contains HTML entities such as <code>&amp;amp;</code>, <code>&amp;lt;</code>, <code>&amp;gt;</code>, or numeric entities (<code>&amp;#</code>), the string is returned as-is. Otherwise, HTML special characters are escaped. The result is marked as a safe string to prevent further auto-escaping.</p>

<p>Use this filter when your data may already be partially escaped and you need to avoid rendering garbled output like <code>&amp;amp;amp;</code>.</p>

<h2>See Also</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/escape">escape</a></li>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/raw">raw</a></li>
</ul>
{% end %}
